parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle surges or revs unexpectedly when the AC is on, causing the vehicle to lunge forward even when the brake is applied, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or revs when the AC is on
especially when slowing down
stopping
or coasting at low speeds; the vehicle jerks when in drive but not applying the gas
then revs with no warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or damage to property.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to hold the vehicle in place
causing it to roll or move even on slight inclines; the vehicle may roll away without warning
even when the parking brake is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floorboard
causing the vehicle to lose braking ability; the failure may cause the vehicle to crash into other objects or vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranded drivers.
symptoms: The power steering light illuminates on the dashboard
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or requires excessive force
the vehicle shakes violently while driving
the vehicle's rear end shifts or pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Passenger Side Sliding Door Handle Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger side sliding door handle can cause difficulty or impossibility in opening the door, potentially leading to safety issues, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door handle breaks
a plastic connector inside the door breaks off
the door cannot be opened.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Recall Repairs for Sliding Door Handles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of recall repairs for sliding door handles can lead to continued safety risks and inconvenience for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Recall notice received
but parts are not available
no estimated time for receiving parts
inability to schedule repair.
